** Project Overview

Something we have to be clear as the first public release, which helps you understand more about why we launch this project, how we develop it, and current develop status.

*** Purpose

In the area of self-hosted Git service, there are some very succeesful products running all around the world, so why we still decide to develop Gogs? How can we compete with them(e.g. gitlab)? What's the view of us in terms of creating the wheel repeatedly?

In the degree of official, our purpose is to take the advantage of Go that builds everything into one binary to setup your own self hosted Git Service. But in my words, I just don't like the products that are existed right now. Because they need a lot of steps and dependencies, or single developer with no anticipated prospect, or no support for cross-platform. And Gogs certainly support a rich number of operating systems because of Go supports.

We have at least two competitor in the long term, gitlab and GitHub Enterprise. So what does Gogs have to compete with them? I don't think I have any yet but one, the binary deployment. You can setup your own Git hosting service with unbelieve simple steps is good enough to keep us being strong.

Many people just hate so-called "creating the wheel repeatedly" without any reason, then they miss the opportunity to be creative. You need to see it in several perspectives. First of all, it's a great thing for learning and practicing skills, especially try something you've never got a chance to try, like we choose [[http://martini.codegangsta.io/][martini]] as our basic framework. Secondly, things that exist do not make us feel satisfied, and we won't give up the chance to improve it.

