*** Current Develop Status

We've released the first public version with many features but only has very low number `v0.2.0` and status `alpha`. I have to say that we do not recommend and Gogs doesn't ready for enterprise usage. So does Gogs just something look nice and useless? Of course not! The core of Git hosting is the Git data, Gogs is kind of stable in this part so every time new version release, you only need to do `copy-paste` upgrade with zero damage of your Git data.

** Getting Started

All documentation is documented in the [[https://github.com/gogits/gogs/wiki][GitHub Wiki]] which helps you understand Gogs more and better.

- For people who just want to have a try, after installing the [[https://github.com/gogits/gogs/wiki/Prerequirements][Prerequirements]], then [[https://github.com/gogits/gogs/wiki/Install-from-binary][Install from binary]] and you're all set.
- If you want to [[https://github.com/gogits/gogs/wiki/Install-from-source][Install from source]], it's also quite easy once you have Go environment.

To be more convenience, Gogs also provides a install page(URL:`/install`) to help you configurate for the first-time run.

